TITLE: Defining GraphQL Query (GET_DOGS)
DESCRIPTION: This snippet defines a GraphQL query named `GET_DOGS` using the `gql` function.  It fetches the `id` and `breed` fields from the `dogs` query. The `gql` function parses the GraphQL query string into a query document usable by Apollo Client.
SOURCE: https://github.com/apollographql/apollo-client/blob/main/docs/source/data/queries.mdx#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: js
CODE:
```
import { gql, useQuery } from '@apollo/client';

const GET_DOGS = gql`
  query GetDogs {
    dogs {
      id
      breed
    }
  }
`;
```

