TITLE: Execute a GraphQL query using ApolloClient
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates executing a GraphQL query directly using the `client.query()` method. The query retrieves a list of locations with their `id`, `name`, `description`, and `photo` properties. The result is then logged to the console.
SOURCE: https://github.com/apollographql/apollo-client/blob/main/docs/source/get-started.mdx#_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: jsx
CODE:
```
// const client = ...

client
  .query({
    query: gql`
      query GetLocations {
        locations {
          id
          name
          description
          photo
        }
      }
    `,
  })
  .then((result) => console.log(result));
```

