TITLE: Using Variables in GraphQL Queries for Reusability
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows how to utilize GraphQL variables to parameterize queries, enhancing reusability and flexibility. It includes an example query with a variable `$dogId` and a JavaScript implementation using `useQuery` hook to pass variable values at runtime.
SOURCE: https://github.com/apollographql/apollo-client/blob/main/docs/source/data/operation-best-practices.mdx#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: GraphQL
CODE:
```
# Recommended âœ…
query GetDog($dogId: ID!) {
  dog(id: $dogId) {
    name
    breed
  }
}

```

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
const GET_DOG = gql`
  query GetDog($dogId: ID!) {
    dog(id: $dogId) {
      name
      breed
    }
  }
`;

function Dog({ id }) {
  const { loading, error, data } = useQuery(GET_DOG, {
    variables: {
      dogId: id
    },
  });
  // ...render component...
}
```

