TITLE: Using fetchMore to Load Additional Data in React
DESCRIPTION: This React component example uses the useQuery hook to execute the FEED_QUERY and includes an onLoadMore handler that calls fetchMore with a new offset based on current feed length. This pattern supports infinite scrolling or 'load more' functionalities by fetching subsequent pages while preserving the existing data in cache.
SOURCE: https://github.com/apollographql/apollo-client/blob/main/docs/source/pagination/core-api.mdx#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
const FeedWithData() {
// ...continuing from above...

// To show a loading indicator during fetchMore
if (loading) return 'Loading...';

return (
    <Feed
      entries={data.feed || []}
      onLoadMore={() => fetchMore({
        variables: {
          offset: data.feed.length
        },
      })}
    />
  );
}
```

