TITLE: Declaring a Parameterized GraphQL Mutation for Adding a To-Do Item - JavaScript/JSX
DESCRIPTION: This code defines a parameterized GraphQL mutation using the gql function to allow adding a new item to a to-do list. The mutation accepts a required type parameter and specifies that the server should return the new object's id and type. This snippet is typically colocated with components that will submit or trigger this mutation. Dependencies: @apollo/client and a GraphQL server implementing the addTodo mutation. Accepts a type string as input and returns an object with id and type fields.
SOURCE: https://github.com/apollographql/apollo-client/blob/main/docs/source/data/mutations.mdx#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: JSX
CODE:
```
import { gql, useMutation } from '@apollo/client';

const ADD_TODO = gql`
  mutation AddTodo($type: String!) {
    addTodo(type: $type) {
      id
      type
    }
  }
`;

```

