TITLE: Configuring Custom RetryLink Strategies (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: This snippet showcases how to create a `RetryLink` with custom retry and delay strategies.  It defines a retry function based on the presence of an error and the operation name and a delay function that calculates the delay using `Math.random()`.  These custom functions provide granular control over retry behavior.
SOURCE: https://github.com/apollographql/apollo-client/blob/main/docs/source/api/link/apollo-link-retry.mdx#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import { RetryLink } from "@apollo/client/link/retry";

const link = new RetryLink({
  attempts: (count, operation, error) => {
    return !!error && operation.operationName != 'specialCase';
  },
  delay: (count, operation, error) => {
    return count * 1000 * Math.random();
  },
});
```

