TITLE: Split Link Based on Operation Type - JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows how to use the `split` function to route subscription operations to a `GraphQLWsLink` and other operations to an `HttpLink`. It uses `getMainDefinition` to determine the operation type from the query. It requires imports from `@apollo/client` and `@apollo/client/link/subscriptions` and assumes a `createClient` function from `graphql-ws`.
SOURCE: https://github.com/apollographql/apollo-client/blob/main/docs/source/api/link/introduction.mdx#_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import { split, HttpLink } from '@apollo/client';
import { getMainDefinition } from '@apollo/client/utilities';
import { GraphQLWsLink } from '@apollo/client/link/subscriptions';
import { createClient } from 'graphql-ws';

export const link = split(
  ({ query }) => {
    const definition = getMainDefinition(query);
    return (
      definition.kind === 'OperationDefinition' &&
      definition.operation === 'subscription'
    );
  },
  new GraphQLWsLink(createClient({ url: 'ws://localhost:3000/subscriptions' })),
  new HttpLink({ uri: 'http://localhost:4000/graphql' })
);

```

