TITLE: Invalidating Cache Fields for Selective Refetching with Apollo Client in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: This snippet uses cache.modify and the INVALIDATE sentinel object within updateCache to mark certain cache fields as invalid, prompting the client to refetch any dependent queries. This is useful for triggering refetch without changing the actual value. Input: cache.modify fields; Output: affected queries refetched. Dependencies: Apollo Client's cache.modify and INVALIDATE support.
