TITLE: Defining a local resolver for toggling a Todo's completed status using Apollo Client
DESCRIPTION: This code demonstrates how to set up a local mutation resolver in Apollo Client to toggle the 'completed' boolean of a Todo item. It utilizes cache.modify and cache.identify to update cache fields efficiently, and the resolver is integrated into an Apollo Client instance.
SOURCE: https://github.com/apollographql/apollo-client/blob/main/docs/source/local-state/local-resolvers.mdx#_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
import { ApolloClient, InMemoryCache } from '@apollo/client';

const client = new ApolloClient({
  cache: new InMemoryCache(),
  resolvers: {
    Mutation: {
      toggleTodo: (_root, variables, { cache }) => {
        cache.modify({
          id: cache.identify({
            __typename: 'TodoItem',
            id: variables.id,
          }),
          fields: {
            completed: value => !value,
          },
        });
        return null;
      },
    },
  },
});
```

