TITLE: Using Fragments in a @nonreactive Context (JSX)
DESCRIPTION: Shows a React `Trail` component (JSX) that uses the `useFragment` hook to read data defined in `TrailFragment` from the cache, identified by `id`. Because the parent `App` component applied `@nonreactive` to the fragment spread in its query, updates to the trail's status (triggered via `useMutation`) only rerender the specific `Trail` component instance, not the parent `App` component.
