TITLE: Adding Todo to Cache Using cache.readQuery & cache.writeQuery - JS
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows how to add a new todo item to a list of todos stored in the Apollo Client cache.  It initializes the cache with an empty list of todos using `cache.writeQuery`.  The `addTodo` resolver reads the existing todos using `cache.readQuery`, adds the new todo to the list, and then updates the cache with the updated list using `cache.writeQuery`. Dependencies include ApolloClient, InMemoryCache and gql from '@apollo/client'.
SOURCE: https://github.com/apollographql/apollo-client/blob/main/docs/source/local-state/local-resolvers.mdx#_snippet_24

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import { ApolloClient, InMemoryCache, gql } from '@apollo/client';

let nextTodoId = 0;

const cache = new InMemoryCache();

cache.writeQuery({
  query: gql`query GetTodos { todos { ... } }`,
  data: { todos: [] },
});

const client = new ApolloClient({
  resolvers: {
    Mutation: {
      addTodo: (_, { text }, { cache }) => {
        const query = gql`
          query GetTodos {
            todos @client {
              id
              text
              completed
            }
          }
        `;

        const previous = cache.readQuery({ query });
        const newTodo = { id: nextTodoId++, text, completed: false, __typename: 'TodoItem' };
        const data = {
          todos: [...previous.todos, newTodo],
        };

        cache.writeQuery({ query, data });
        return newTodo;
      },
    },
  },
});
```

