TITLE: Index.ts and Index.js: Implementing split link with Apollo Client
DESCRIPTION: This code initializes both HTTP and WebSocket links, then uses Apollo Client's split function to direct queries/mutations over HTTP and subscriptions over WebSocket. It illustrates combining links based on the operation type for optimized connection management.
SOURCE: https://github.com/apollographql/apollo-client/blob/main/docs/source/data/subscriptions.mdx#_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: TypeScript
CODE:
```
import { split, HttpLink } from '@apollo/client';
import { getMainDefinition } from '@apollo/client/utilities';
import { GraphQLWsLink } from '@apollo/client/link/subscriptions';
import { createClient } from 'graphql-ws';

const httpLink = new HttpLink({
  uri: 'http://localhost:4000/graphql'
});

const wsLink = new GraphQLWsLink(createClient({
  url: 'ws://localhost:4000/subscriptions',
}));

// The split function takes three parameters:
//
// * A function that's called for each operation to execute
// * The Link to use for an operation if the function returns a "truthy" value
// * The Link to use for an operation if the function returns a "falsy"" value
const splitLink = split(
  ({ query }) => {
    const definition = getMainDefinition(query);
    return (
      definition.kind === 'OperationDefinition' &&
      definition.operation === 'subscription'
    );
  },
  wsLink,
  httpLink,
);
```

