TITLE: Updating Apollo Client Cache with 'options.updateQueries' (Deprecated)
DESCRIPTION: This snippet discusses the use of 'options.updateQueries' to update specific queries in the cache based on mutation results. It demonstrates defining reducer functions keyed by query names, which receive previous data and mutation result to produce updated data, following Redux reducer patterns.
SOURCE: https://github.com/apollographql/apollo-client/blob/main/docs/source/api/react/hoc.mdx#_snippet_40

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
export default graphql(
  gql`
  mutation SubmitComment ($text: String!) {
    submitComment(text: $text) { ... }
  }
`,
  {
    options: {
      updateQueries: {
        Comments: (previousData, { mutationResult }) => {
          const newComment = mutationResult.data.submitComment;
          return {
            ...previousData,
            entry: {
              ...previousData.entry,
              comments: [newComment, ...previousData.entry.comments],
            },
          };
        },
      },
    },
  },
)(MyComponent);
```

