TITLE: Updating Apollo Client Cache Using 'options.update' Function
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to update the Apollo Client cache after a mutation using the 'update' function within the options object. It reads query data with 'readQuery', modifies the data, and writes it back with 'writeQuery' to update the cache reactively.
SOURCE: https://github.com/apollographql/apollo-client/blob/main/docs/source/api/react/hoc.mdx#_snippet_37

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
const query = gql`query GetAllTodos { todos { ... } }`;

export default graphql(
  gql`
  mutation CreateTodo ($text: String!) {
    createTodo(text: $text) { ... }
  }
`,
  {
    options: {
      update: (proxy, { data: { createTodo } }) => {
        const data = proxy.readQuery({ query });
        data.todos.push(createTodo);
        proxy.writeQuery({ query, data });
      },
    },
  },
)(MyComponent);
```

