TITLE: Nested Fields Configuration
DESCRIPTION: This code demonstrates how to configure `removeTypenameFromVariables` to keep `__typename` for deeply nested fields within different input types, including multiple levels of nesting. It also includes array handling in the `widgets` property.
SOURCE: https://github.com/apollographql/apollo-client/blob/main/docs/source/api/link/apollo-link-remove-typename.mdx#_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: ts
CODE:
```
import { removeTypenameFromVariables, KEEP } from '@apollo/client/link/remove-typename';

const removeTypenameLink = removeTypenameFromVariables({
  except: {
    // Keep __typename for `bar` and `baz` fields on any variable
    // declared as a `FooInput` type
    FooInput: {
      bar: KEEP,
      baz: KEEP,
    },

    // Keep __typename for the `baz.qux` field on any variable
    // declared as a `BarInput` type
    BarInput: {
      baz: {
        qux: KEEP
      }
    },

    // Keep __typename on `bar.baz` and `bar.qux.foo` fields for any
    // variable declared as a `BazInput` type
    BazInput: {
      bar: {
        baz: KEEP,
        qux: {
          foo: KEEP
        }
      }
    },
  }
});
```

